President Joe Biden has declared a major disaster in the state of New Jersey and authorized federal aid to assist with recovery efforts following the remnants of Hurricane Ida. The declaration makes federal funding available to individuals and businesses in the counties of Bergen, Gloucester, Hunterdon, Middlesex, Passaic, and Somerset. Assistance can include grants for temporary housing, home repairs, and low-cost loans for uninsured property losses. Federal funding is also available for emergency work, facility repairs, and hazard mitigation measures. Patrick Cornbill has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Damage assessments are ongoing, and additional counties may be designated for assistance. Residents and business owners in the designated counties can apply for assistance online or by phone. The FEMA News Desk can provide further information.